column11: Let’s talk about my “Giant frog” Dump’s eyes and why they sometimes look different. Dumpy is an Australian whites tree frog and like most frogs she is nocturnal, and because of this her eyes are very good at seeing in the dark, frogs pupils will expand to let in much more light then a humans eye can. Depending on how much light is around her her eyes will adapt by opening and closing the pupil giving the eye a completely different appearance. This is why Dumpy’s eyes may appear different throughout our videos. If you would like to learn more about my “Giant” pet frog tap on the folder at the the bottom of this video. Consider hitting the plus icon, and check out what else I’m up to. We appreciate your support. #giantfrog #dumpytreefrog  #petfrog #frogeyes #learnontiktok

column11: Who would've ever thought that the guy who was just working for a pizza-hut branch would actually end up buying the damn branch?
column13: Who would've ever thought that the guy who was just working for a pizza-hut branch would actually end up buying the damn branch? Nobody, nobody would ever believe it until they'd see it. But that's exactly what happened to me. Unlike most people, I didn't actually have an issue of """"working hard."""" I could see the difference immediately between myself and my other workmates. I did everything I could to learn more, earn more, and have more. From 2012 - 2017, I was working 120-170hrs a week. Anything below that didn't feel like work to me at all. Now I know that this isn't your """"take it easy"""" advice, but I had a dream - and I knew that I had to work hard for it. SO I WORKED HARD. If you want live a life of """"safety"""" but without freedom - then remain in a Fvcking Job. But if you want to live life to the fullest, then COMMIT TO GROWTH. You'll have to take risks... You'll have to take painful punches from life... You'll have to make sacrifices... And you'll have to be consistent. Do this, and you'll live a life less than 1% of people will get to experience. #investments #moneymotivation  #multimillionaire  #cashflow  #entrepreneurship  #business  #entrepreneurlife  #businessowner  #financialfreedom  #india  #indianbusinessowner  #businessmindset  #fypシ #foryoupage

column13: Fusion Food Series : Kimchi Gyros Ingredients - Kimchi Pita bread* - Tzatziki* - Marinade Chicken* - Onions - French fries (optional) - Tomatoes - parsley Kimchi Peeta* Recipe - Mix 7g yeast, 10g sugar, and 240g water - Add 350g of Bread flour, a pinch of salt and mix with yeast water - Fermentation at room temperature for 1~2 hours - Cut it into quarters and ferment for 20 minutes - Put the kimchi in the batter and make it round and ferment for 20 minutes - Bake in a frying pan over medium-low heat Tzatziki* Recipe (based on 2~3 servings) - Ingredients: 1/2 cucumber, 200ml yogurt, 1t of minced garlic, 1T of lemon juice, 1T of olive oil, dill (parsley),pinch of salt - Put cucumber in the grinder Grind and season with salt - After 10 minutes, drain the cucumber and mix with yogurt - If you put all the remaining ingredients Marinade Chicken* (two chicken Thigh) - Marinade: 1/2 cup yogurt, lemon juice, 1/4 cup olive oil, salt, minced garlic, paprika powder, cumin, cinnamon, pepper 1T  - Marinade for 1 hour - Cook 180'c oven for 15 minutes   Recipe - Kimchi pita bread -> Tzatziki -> Chicken -> French Fries -> Onion -> Tomato -> Parsley 재료 - 김치 피타 빵* - 차지키 소스* - 치킨 고기* - 양파 - 감자튀김(생략가능) - 토마토 - 파슬리 김치 피타 레시피 - 7g 이스트, 10g 설탕, 240g 물을 섞는다 - 강력분 350g, 소금 한 꼬집을 넣고 이스트 물과 섞는다 - 1~2시간 상온에서 발효하기 - 4등분하고 20분 발효해준다 - 반죽에 볶은 김치를 넣고 동그랗게 만들어주고 20분 발효해준다 - 후라이팬에 중약불로 구워준다 차지키 소스 레시피 (4인분 기준) - 재료 : 오이 1개, 요거트 250ml, 다진 마늘 1스푼, 레몬 주스 2스푼, 엑스트라 버진 올리브 오일 1스푼, 딜(파슬리) 10g, 소금 한 꼬집 - 오이 1개를 그라인더에 갈아주고 소금 간을 한다 - 10분 뒤 오이의 물기를 없애주고 요거트와 섞어준다 - 남은 재료를 다 넣으면 완성 치킨(닭다리살 2개) - 마리네이드 : 요거트 1/2컵, 레몬주스, 오일 1/4컵 소금, 다진마늘, 파프리카파우더, 큐민, 시나몬, 후추 1T  - 1시간 마리네이드 - 180’c 오븐 15분 익히기   레시피 - 피타 빵-> 차지키 -> 치킨 -> 감자튀김 -> 채썬 양파 -> 토마토  -> 파슬리#koreanfood #tiktokfood
